SECTION 1 — NATURE OF THIS SOFTWARE
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
This repository contains a Proof of Concept (PoC) implementation of malicious
software ("Malware"). It is published exclusively for the following legitimate
purposes:

  (a) Security research and vulnerability analysis
  (b) Academic study and coursework in cybersecurity
  (c) Controlled red team / penetration testing exercises with explicit
      written consent from all relevant parties
  (d) Development of detection signatures, antivirus rules, or defensive tooling
  (e) Personal education and technical skill development in a sandboxed environment

Any use outside of the purposes enumerated above is EXPRESSLY PROHIBITED.


SECTION 2 — PERMISSIONS
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Subject to the conditions in Section 3, you are permitted to:

  ✓  Read and study this source code for educational purposes
  ✓  Fork or clone this repository solely for educational or PoC use cases
  ✓  Modify the code within a private, isolated research environment
  ✓  Reference or cite this work in academic papers or security write-ups,
     with proper attribution (see Section 3)
  ✓  Use output artifacts (e.g., signatures, detection rules) derived from
     analysis of this software in defensive security tooling


SECTION 3 — CONDITIONS & RESTRICTIONS
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Use of this software, in whole or in part, in any form, is conditioned upon
strict compliance with ALL of the following:

  3.1  ATTRIBUTION REQUIRED
       Any fork, derivative work, academic paper, write-up, presentation,
       blog post, or tool that references, uses, or is derived from this
       software MUST include clear and prominent attribution to the original
       author in the following form:

           Based on work by Telos — https://github.com/telosGit/tarball

       Attribution must appear in the README, file header, or credits section
       of any derivative work. Removal or obfuscation of this attribution
       constitutes a violation of this license.

  3.2  NO MALICIOUS DEPLOYMENT
       You MAY NOT execute, deploy, install, or distribute this software on
       any system, network, device, or infrastructure that you do not own
       or have explicit written authorization to test. Doing so is illegal
       under the Computer Fraud and Abuse Act (18 U.S.C. § 1030), the UK
       Computer Misuse Act 1990, and equivalent laws in most jurisdictions.

  3.3  NO WEAPONIZATION
       You MAY NOT use this software, or any derivative thereof, as a
       component of an attack, campaign, botnet, exploit kit, ransomware
       operation, or any offensive tooling intended for unauthorized use
       against real targets.

  3.4  NO COMMERCIAL USE
       This software may not be sold, sublicensed, incorporated into
       commercial products, or used in any revenue-generating context
       without explicit written permission from the copyright holder.

  3.5  EDUCATIONAL / PoC FORKING ONLY
       Forking or cloning this repository is only permitted if the fork is
       maintained strictly for educational or PoC purposes. Forks found to
       be used in violation of this license — including but not limited to
       malicious deployment, weaponization, or obfuscation of origin — are
       subject to DMCA takedown and legal action.

  3.6  ISOLATION REQUIREMENT
       Any execution of this software must occur within an isolated
       environment (e.g., air-gapped VM, sandboxed container, controlled
       lab network). Execution on production systems or live networks is
       strictly prohibited.


